# Quality Gates

Single source of truth for merge-blocking engineering checks.

## Hard Requirements

- Do: require lint, format, type-check, and tests to pass before merge.
- Do: enforce minimum 80% code coverage unless repo explicitly documents an
  approved temporary exception.
- Do: run checks in CI and keep local parity scripts available where practical.
- Do not: bypass failing checks without explicit approval and documented follow-up.
- Why: consistent quality gates prevent regressions and reduce integration risk.

## Opinionated Defaults

- Use pre-commit hooks for fast local feedback.
- Keep CI jobs deterministic and aligned with local scripts.
- Fail fast on lint/type errors before running expensive integration suites.

## Exceptions

- Emergency hotfixes can ship with a temporary gate waiver only when:
  - incident response requires immediate mitigation, and
  - a follow-up issue is created to restore full compliance.
- For legacy repositories below target coverage, allow staged thresholds if they
  are documented and trend upward.

## Acceptance Checks

- CI workflow includes lint, type checks, and test jobs.
- Coverage threshold is configured and enforced.
- PRs include validation output or references to CI run results.
